> Headings:

<body>
  <h1>Heading 1</h1>                            <!-- Biggest -->
  <h2>Heading 2</h2>
  <h3>Heading 3</h3>
  <h4>Heading 4</h4>
  <h5>Heading 5</h5>
  <h6>Heading 6</h6>                            <!-- Smallest -->
</body>

<br/>                                           <!-- line break -->
<hr/>                                           <!-- insert horizontal line -->

__________________________________________________________________________________________________

 __        __        __   __        __   __        __     
|__)  /\  |__)  /\  / _` |__)  /\  |__) / _` |__| /__`    
|    /~~\ |  \ /~~\ \__> |  \ /~~\ |    \__> |  | .__/    
                                                          
> Paragraphs:

<p>
   This is a paragraph <br>
   with mulitple <br>
   lines 
</p>

__________________________________________________________________________________________________

___  ___     ___           ___ ___       __   __   __  
 |  |__  \_/  |      |\/| |__   |  |__| /  \ |  \ /__` 
 |  |___ / \  |      |  | |___  |  |  | \__/ |__/ .__/ 
                                                       
> Text methods:

<p>This is regular text </p>
<p><b>bold text </b></p>
<p><big> big text </big></p>
<p><i> italic text </i></p>
<p><small> small text </small></p>
<p><strong> strong text </strong></p>
<p><sub> subscripted text </sub></p>
<p><sup> superscripted text </sup></p>
<p><ins> inserted text </ins></p>
<p><del> deleted text </del></p>

__________________________________________________________________________________________________

        __  ___  __  
|    | /__`  |  /__` 
|___ | .__/  |  .__/ 
                     
> Unordered Lists:

<ul>
   <li>Tea</li>
   <li>Sugar</li>
   <li>Milk</li>
</ul>

> Ordered Lists:

<ol>
   <li>Tea</li>
   <li>Sugar</li>
   <li>Milk</li>
</ol>

__________________________________________________________________________________________________

 __          __  
|  \ | \  / /__` 
|__/ |  \/  .__/ 
                 
> Divs:
- It acts as a generic container and has no effect on the content unless it is styled by CSS.

<div>
   <p>This is a paragraph inside a div</p>                      <!-- inside "div" tags -->
</div>

_________________________________________________

Aligned Divs:

<body>
      <div align = center>
           <p align = center>There can be any text </p>
      </div>
</body>

_________________________________________________

Style Divs:

<style> 
   div {
      border: 1px solid black;                                  <!-- Setting a CSS style  in the "style" tags -->
      padding: 2px;
   }
</style>
<div>
   <div>
      <p>This is a paragraph inside stylized divs</p>           <!-- Paragraph gets styled twice because its in two "div"s -->
   </div>
</div>

__________________________________________________________________________________________________

          __   ___  __                    __  
|__| \ / |__) |__  |__) |    | |\ | |__/ /__` 
|  |  |  |    |___ |  \ |___ | | \| |  \ .__/ 
                                              
> HyperLinks:

<a href="link.html"> This Is my Link </a>                       <!-- "This Is my link" will be clickable and displayed in blue, linking to the "link.html" file -->

<a href="example.com" target="_blank">This is my link </a>      <!-- Giving a _blank value to your attribute will have the link open in a new window or new tab -->

__________________________________________________________________________________________________

              __   ___  __  
|  |\/|  /\  / _` |__  /__` 
|  |  | /~~\ \__> |___ .__/ 
                            
> Images:

<img src="MyImage.jpeg">                                                             <!-- adding the source of the image -->

<img src="MyImage.jpeg" width="500" height"300" alt="This is my image alt text">     <!-- adding the source of the image, with custom dimensions and alt text -->

__________________________________________________________________________________________________

___       __        ___  __  
 |   /\  |__) |    |__  /__` 
 |  /~~\ |__) |___ |___ .__/ 
                             
> HTML tables:

<body>
    <table>                                 <!-- Opening the table tag -->
        <th>                                <!-- table heading -->
            <td>Name</td>                   <!-- table data -->
            <td>Price</td>                  <!-- second collumn in this table row -->
        </th>
        <tr>                                <!-- adding a table row -->
            <td>Item 1</td>                 
            <td>£5.00</td>                  
        </tr>
        <tr>                                <!-- creating a new table row -->
            <td>Item 2</td>
            <td>£9.00</td>
        </tr>
    </table>
</body>

_________________________________________________

<table border="2">                              <!-- creates a border to visualise the table -->
    <tr>
        <td>item 1</td>
        <td>item 2</td>
        <td>item 3</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>info <br /></td>
        <td colspan="2"><br />more info</td>    <!-- The second and third collum on the second row will merge together into one-->
    </tr>
</table>
__________________________________________________________________________________________________

